Installation    
    Windows
      - We just download the file from the official website safe version!
      - Unzip the files in a folder, e.g c:/php
      - config windows path variable to tell windows that php is inside that 
        custom folder:
        - search for environment variables => open the tab
        - Variable: Path => click and edit => add new variable => C:\php !
        Check the environment variables in terminal:
         - C:\Users\USUARIO>echo %PATH%

    Check php Installation
      - Restart terminal or open a new one
        php -v 

